{
  "text": "The first experiment to provide results obtained with a ratio method was NEOS [CITATION_1] , in South Korea, which however has only one fixed detector at \u223c 25 m from the reactor core and uses the DayaBay flux observations at much bigger distances (the reactor composition is similar) in order to obtain the ratio. A second experiment of this kind is DANSS [CITATION_2] , in Russia, which instead has a movable detector that can be moved to three different positions, at distances between \u223c 10.5 and 12.5 m from the reactor core. From the fluxes at these three positions, two ratios can be computed.",
